    MRealTextField
    public class RealTextField
extends javax.swing.JTextField
implements NumericPlainDocument.InsertErrorListener, java.io.Serializable, java.awt.datatransfer.ClipboardOwner, ModelDependent
    The RealTextField is a JTextField that is specialized for working with Real values and extensions from the Number package. A RealTextField is created like a regular TextField. However, getValue() returns a Real Object instead of a String Object. The default Real is dimensionless, so storing the entered value into a value with units should involve a convert( double value ) call on the target to preserve the entered value.
